{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9af7345d-526d-4e08-813c-0e6e0a6e0cd1","content":"Here are **3 evaluation performance issues** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. 🔴 File I/O property function (line 13, `EvalHeavy.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n`System.IO.File::ReadAllText` runs during **evaluation**, not execution. This blocks the MSBuild evaluation phase with disk I/O. If the file grows or is on a slow volume, every evaluation pays the cost — including IDE design-time builds.\n\n**Fix:** Read the file in a target at execution time using `ReadLinesFromFile`, or remove it if unused at build time.\n\n---\n\n### 2. 🟠 Expensive wildcard glob (line 9, `EvalHeavy.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` walks the **entire directory tree** during evaluation. This is especially costly if the repo contains large folders (e.g., `node_modules`, test fixtures, artifacts). The SDK already provides implicit globs for compilable files, so this blanket glob is likely unnecessary.\n\n**Fix:** Narrow the pattern to specific extensions (e.g., `**\\*.txt`) or add large directories to `DefaultItemExcludes` early in evaluation.\n\n---\n\n### 3. 🟡 Deep import chain (3 levels)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nThe chained imports add evaluation overhead proportional to depth. At 3 levels this is moderate, but it compounds in a larger repo. Each import adds a file-existence check and parse cycle.\n\n**Fix:** Flatten into a single `.props` file if the separation isn't needed for reuse across projects.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** The file-read property function (#1) and the broad glob (#2) are the most impactful. The import chain (#3) is minor here but worth watching as the project grows.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"147af169-0dc7-4385-8cea-082b261950d4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze the evaluation performance issues in this project.","outputTokens":536,"requestId":"0403:28D016:630862E:6BD8FD8:69F01000"},"id":"e97fcda1-27cc-4ebc-95fb-0946f9e022e1","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:40:29.328Z","parentId":"cd9f5a06-83af-45b5-b63d-6c5520f325aa"}
